<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="5973b951-0bb3-5fbf-b254-38ff20712e97" activityNameId="c5dee60f-8be5-44cf-a6ae-b51520c713ec" parentActivityId="f7e1a11b-c15d-5047-bcc0-8e939c055a61" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">sodium hydrogen sulfite production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Sodium hydrogen sulfite sodium bisulfite</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of sodium hydrogen sulfite and includes materials, energy uses, infrastructure, and emissions.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of sodium hydrogen sulfite from sulfur dioxide in Europe. Sodium hydrogen sulfite (NaHSO3) is not known in the solid state. By concentrating an aqueous solution, solid sodium disulfite crystallizes. Sodium hydrogen sulfite is oxidized in air. It is produced by reaction of sodium hydroxide with sulfur dioxide according to the following reaction:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">NaOH + SO2 → NaHSO3</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">This dataset is based on stoechiometric calculations as well as approximations based on data from a large chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Frischknecht R., Jungbluth N., Althaus H.-J., Doka G., Dones R., Heck T., Hellweg S., Hischier R., Nemecek T., Rebitzer G. and Spielmann M. (2007) Overview and Methodology. Final report ecoinvent v2.0 No. 1. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH, retrieved from: www.ecoinvent.org.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">José Jiménez Barberá, Adolf Metzger, Manfred Wolf: Sulfites, Thiosulfates, and Dithionites. Published online: 2003. In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Seventh Edition, 2004 Electronic Release (ed. Fiedler E., Grossmann G., Kersebohm D., Weiss G. and Witte C.). 7 th Electronic Release Edition. Wiley InterScience, New York, Online-Version under: DOI: 10.1002/14356007.a25_477</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The inventory is modelled for Europe but is assumed to be representative of the global production. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Reaction of sulfur dioxide and sodium hydroxide.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time of publications. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
