        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The global production volume is extrapolated from the European production volume based on reports from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council), and the American Chemistry Council.  
According to Cefic (2016a) the global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3 534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per region are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (US, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the US total sales, which amount to 518.7 billion euros out of the global 3 534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported by the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to which the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 
European production volume:
Estimated value. According to the European Chemical Agency, the consumption of Sodium hydrogensulfite for the year of 2016 is estimated to be 550000000 kg. The aforementioned value is the average of the range given in the literature. According to the European Chemical Industry Council (Cefic, 2016a), the total sales of chemicals of the European Union in 2016 amounted to 519 billion euros. Chemical imports were valued at 91 billion euros for the first 11 months of 2016. Based on this, the value for the total imports for the year 2016 was extrapolated, yielding a value of 99.3 billion euros. Furthermore, Cefic (2016b) reports a trade surplus (exports-imports) of 46.4 billion euros (once again extrapolated for the whole year using the value of 42 billion euros for the first 11 months of 2016). Considering all the aforementioned information, the total chemical consumption in the EU is calculated to be 472.6 billion euros (total sales-exports+imports). It is therefore calculated that production is 110% of consumption. This value is used to scale the information on chemical consumption to production. The European production volume is therefore 605000000 kg. Since no data were found for the global production this value was scaled accordingly.

References:
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html
European Chemical Agency, Brief profile of Sodium hydrogensulfite, Accessible at: https://echa.europa.eu/brief-profile/-/briefprofile/100.028.680
Cefic 2016a. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
Cefic 2016b. 2016: EU chemicals output posts positive growth for third year running. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Documents/RESOURCES/Chemical%20Trends%20Report/March-2017-Cefic-Chemicals-Trends-Report.pdf</productionVolumeComment>
